data.current_description: List the jobs of a project. To list the jobs of a project in a region, we recommend using `projects.locations.jobs.list` with a [regional endpoint] (https://cloud.google.com/dataflow/docs/concepts/regional-endpoints). To list the all jobs across all regions, use `projects.jobs.aggregated`. Using `projects.jobs.list` is not recommended, because you can only get the list of jobs that are running in `us-central1`. `projects.locations.jobs.list` and `projects.jobs.list` support filtering the list of jobs by name. Filtering by name isn't supported by `projects.jobs.aggregated`.
data.summary_suggestion: List Cloud Dataflow jobs in project
data.description_suggestion: Lists Cloud Dataflow jobs in the specified project. Note: This operation only returns jobs running in us-central1. For region-specific job listings, use projects.locations.jobs.list with a regional endpoint. For jobs across all regions, use projects.jobs.aggregated. Supports filtering jobs by name. Returns a ListJobsResponse containing job summaries and pagination information. Recommended for legacy workflows only; regional endpoints are preferred for new implementations.

data.current_description: Creates a Cloud Dataflow job. data.current_description: Updates the state of an existing Cloud Dataflow job. To update the state of an existing job, we recommend using `projects.locations.jobs.update` with a [regional endpoint] (https://cloud.google.com/dataflow/docs/concepts/regional-endpoints). Using `projects.jobs.update` is not recommended, as you can only update the state of jobs that are running in `us-central1`.
data.summary_suggestion: Update Cloud Dataflow job state
data.description_suggestion: Updates the state of an existing Cloud Dataflow job. Accepts a Job object with updated configuration or state changes (e.g., cancellation, draining). Requires projectId and jobId parameters. Note: This operation only updates jobs running in us-central1. For jobs in other regions, use projects.locations.jobs.update with a regional endpoint. Returns the updated Job object. Side effects include state transitions (e.g., RUNNING to CANCELLED) and potential worker behavior changes. Recommended for legacy workflows only.

data.current_description: Request detailed information about the execution status of the job. EXPERIMENTAL. This API is subject to change or removal without notice.
data.summary_suggestion: Get detailed job execution status information
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves detailed execution status information for a Dataflow job, including task-level metrics and progress. EXPERIMENTAL. This API is subject to change or removal without notice. Returns execution details containing worker metrics, task status, and progress information.

message: Operation 'dataflow.projects.locations.jobs.messages.list' has semantic quality issues: vague_summary, vague_description, missing_output_details. Missing summary. Description is confusing and mixes endpoint recommendations with operation purpose. Clarified that this lists messages (not just requests status), specified return value (paginated message list), and reorganized endpoint guidance for better AI agent understanding of regional vs legacy endpoints.

data.current_description: Request the job status. data.current_description: List the jobs of a project. To list the jobs of a project in a region, we recommend using `projects.locations.jobs.list` with a [regional endpoint] (https://cloud.google.com/dataflow/docs/concepts/regional-endpoints). To list the all jobs across all regions, use `projects.jobs.aggregated`. Using `projects.jobs.list` is not recommended, because you can only get the list of jobs that are running in `us-central1`. `projects.locations.jobs.list` and `projects.jobs.list` support filtering the list of jobs by name. Filtering by name isn't supported by `projects.jobs.aggregated`.

Returns a ListJobsResponse containing an array of Job objects matching the filter criteria, with pagination support. Use regional endpoints for location-specific queries; this operation only returns jobs in the specified location, not across all regions.
